   <mods:abstract>The original state constitution will be forwarded to Yates to be deposited
            in the office of the Secretary of State. Part of the preamble and the 27th and 28th
            sections are missing; they were probably written on separate pieces of paper and may yet
            be recovered. The minutes and papers of the Provincial Congress, Committees of Safety
            and Convention in the early part of the Revolution, which came to him on the death of
            his uncle, are in the process of being arranged and transcribed. The completion of this
            task required a skillful and diligent clerk; asks if Yates has the authority to furnish
            the means for employing such help.</mods:abstract>
